EXTRACTED VALUE: Two Worlds aims high and delivers a flawed-yet-decent role-playing game that is lengthy and occasionally fun.
If you judge TMNT on its own merits as a platform-hopper with a dash of semi-imaginative combat thrown in, then it's a fine game.
The tragedy is that an earlier relesae date would have seen this be a real smash hit. [Aug 2008, p.80]
Whatever critical punishment you can level at the game, its gameplay core packs enough punch to survive your flurry.
The game modes, including my personal favorite the All Star weekend, are a joy to play and you will not get bored fast with Live 07.
